<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="94" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,403,898]" pageId="1" pageNumber="94">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,319,727,753]" pageId="1" pageNumber="94">Variation.</emphasis>
The female from Jebel Shams has a reduced yellow band on T2, which covers only the apical half of the tergite (
<figureCitation box="[279,344,763,789]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–3" captionStartId="1.[151,264,1590,1614]" captionTargetBox="[154,1432,919,1564]" captionTargetId="figure-317@1.[154,1432,919,1564]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1–3. 1. Ctenagenia vespiformis ♀ dark colour pattern, body length 19.5 mm; 2.Ctenagenia vespiformis ♀ usual coulour pattern, boldy length 20.0 mm; 3. Ctenagenia wahisi ♀ holotype, body length 20.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6637293" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6637293/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="94">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). T2 is all yellow in the remaining specimens, apart from the black apex (
<figureCitation box="[1173,1242,763,789]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–3" captionStartId="1.[151,264,1590,1614]" captionTargetBox="[154,1432,919,1564]" captionTargetId="figure-317@1.[154,1432,919,1564]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1–3. 1. Ctenagenia vespiformis ♀ dark colour pattern, body length 19.5 mm; 2.Ctenagenia vespiformis ♀ usual coulour pattern, boldy length 20.0 mm; 3. Ctenagenia wahisi ♀ holotype, body length 20.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6637293" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6637293/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="94">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="94" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,403,898]" pageId="1" pageNumber="94">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,664,799,825]" pageId="1" pageNumber="94">Distribution in the Arabian peninsula.</emphasis>
The species was previously found in 
<collectingCountry box="[1101,1182,800,826]" name="Yemen" pageId="1" pageNumber="94">Yemen</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1195,1343,799,825]" name="Saudi Arabia" pageId="1" pageNumber="94">Saudi Arabia</collectingCountry>
and the 
<collectingCountry box="[151,398,835,861]" name="United Arab Emirates" pageId="1" pageNumber="94">United Arab Emirates</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Gadallah, N. S. &amp; Schmid-Egger, C. &amp; Brothers, D. J." box="[414,650,835,862]" pageId="1" pageNumber="94" pagination="153 - 175" refId="ref1997" refString="Gadallah, N. S., Schmid-Egger, C. &amp; Brothers, D. J. (2020) Biodiversity of the aculeate wasps (Hymenoptera: Aculeata) of the Arabian Peninsule: Vespoidea, Pompilidae. Zootaxa, 4574 (1), 153 - 175. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4754.1.16" type="journal article" year="2020">
Gadallah 
<emphasis box="[525,575,835,861]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="94">et al</emphasis>
. 2020
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Schmid-Egger, C." box="[663,894,835,861]" pageId="1" pageNumber="94" pagination="350 - 416" refId="ref2060" refString="Schmid-Egger, C. (2017) Order Hymenoptera, family. Pompilidae. Arthropod fauna of the UAE, 6, 350 - 416." type="journal article" year="2017">Schmid-Egger 2017</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Klug" baseAuthorityYear="1834" box="[913,1180,835,862]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Ctenagenia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="94" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vespiformis">
<emphasis box="[913,1180,835,862]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="94">Ctenagenia vespiformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is new to the fauna of 
<collectingCountry box="[151,219,871,897]" name="Oman" pageId="1" pageNumber="94">Oman</collectingCountry>
and was recorded from both the northern provinces and 
<collectingRegion box="[854,1038,871,897]" country="Oman" name="Zufar" pageId="1" pageNumber="94">Dhofar province</collectingRegion>
in the extreme south of 
<collectingCountry box="[1311,1383,871,897]" name="Oman" pageId="1" pageNumber="94">Oman</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
